10/07/2003
OHRID, Macedonia -- A four-day meeting of the heads of military intelligence and counterintelligence services of Macedonia, Albania and Croatia started Wednesday (9 July) in Ohrid.
Participants are exchanging experiences in the fights against terrorism and against trafficking in weapons, goods and humans.They are also discussing measures to prevent regional destabilisation.
The meeting is part of the Adriatic Charter signed by the three countries and the United States.
In other news, a delegation from Serbia, led by Deputy Prime Minister Zarko Korac, spent the day in Skopje Wednesday, discussing cultural and social policy projects.
(MIA, Makfax - 09/07/03)
